## Iteration Complete

**MIXA-017: RAG chat pipeline** — DONE

### What was implemented:

**`packages/ai-pipeline/src/pipeline.ts`** — Full RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) pipeline:
- **`ragQuery()`** — Non-streaming: retrieve → pack context → generate → extract citations
- **`ragStream()`** — Streaming: same pipeline but yields tokens as they arrive
- **`packContext()`** — Greedy context window packing with token budgets, prioritizing highest-scored chunks
- **`buildSystemPrompt()`** — Constructs system prompt with numbered `[1]`, `[2]` source citations
- **`extractCitations()`** — Parses citation markers from LLM response, maps to source items
- Supports scoped chat (filter by projects/tags)
- Supports multi-turn conversations via chat history
- Graceful fallback when no context matches

**`packages/ai-pipeline/src/pipeline.test.ts`** — 23 unit tests:
- `packContext`: empty results, single chunk, sequential indices, score-based ordering, token budget limits, deduplication, metadata preservation
- `buildSystemPrompt`: fallback prompt, source formatting, null domain handling
- `extractCitations`: single/multiple citations, deduplication, non-existent indices, sort order, markdown content, snippet truncation

Also fixed: hybrid search default weights aligned to PRD spec (0.7/0.3 vector/FTS).

